The three people suspected of kidnapping Amy'Leigh de Jager are set to appear in the Vanderbijlpark Magistrates Court this morning. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three people arrested in the kidnapping Amy'Leigh de Jager are expected to appear in the Vanderbijlpark Magistrates court on Monday.
The six-year-old was taken from her school last week but then released. READ: Three arrested for Amy'Leigh kidnapping One of the suspects is a teacher at her school and is known to the parents. Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi said the Department supports the decision to suspend the teacher involved in the kidnapping of the Grade R learner. "We have endorsed the decision that has been taken by the SGB to immediately suspend the teacher concerned."